def: A dull, lusterless surface in certain of the arts, as gilding,metal work, glassmaking, etc.
A woodpecker; -- called also specht, spekt, spight. [Obs. orProv. Eng.]
A wheel with cogs or teeth; a gear wheel. See Illust. ofGearing.
The interval or space between two pilasters. Elmes.
An alkaloid, first found in white cinchona bark.
One of the descendants of Esau or Edom, the brother of Jacob;an Idumean.
